{"title_page": "Bangladesh Ordnance Factories", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Bangladesh Ordnance Factories \n| logo = BangladeshOrdnanceFactoriesLogo.png\n| logo_size  = 150px\n| logo_alt  =\n| logo_caption  =\n| native_name  = {{lang-bn|\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u09b8\u09ae\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 \u0995\u09be\u09b0\u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09be}}\n| type  =  [[State-owned enterprise]]\n| location  = \n| founded  = {{start date and age|1970|4|6}}\n| location_city = [[Gazipur, Dhaka Division|Gazipur]], [[Dhaka Division]]\n| location_country = [[Bangladesh]]\n| area_served  = Bangladesh\n| key_people = \n| products = [[Firearm]]s, [[Artillery]], [[fuse (explosives)|Fuses]], [[Detonators]], [[Explosives]].\n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| owner = [[Bangladesh Army]]\n| num_employees =\n| parent = \n| subsid = \n| division = \n| homepage = [http://www.bof.gov.bd www.bof.gov.bd]\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Bangladesh Ordnance Factories''' '''(BOF)''' is the largest industrial supplier of the [[Bangladesh Army]]. Situated in [[Gazipur]], it produces arms, ammunition, and equipment for the [[Bangladesh Armed Forces]].\n\nThe current Commandant of Bangladesh Ordnance Factories is Major General Sheikh Pasha Habib Uddin, Afwc, psc\n\n==History==\nEstablishment of Bangladesh Ordnance Factory commenced in 1968 with the technical and financial assistance of People's Republic of China. It was inaugurated on 6 April 1970. Although it suffered considerable damage during the [[Bangladesh Liberation War]] in 1971, its capabilities have been restored and expanded since.\n\nIn 1982-1983 BMR (Balancing, Modernization, Replacement) works started which was completed in 1987. After the BMR the yearly production target of the factory was determined to be 2500 rifles and 15 million ammunition per annum. Project on establishment of \u2018Automatic Assault Rifle BD-08\u2019 factory was under taken in 2004-2005 and it was successfully implemented in the year 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/|title=Bangladesh Ordnance  Factories|work=bof.gov.bd}}</ref>\n\n==Technology==\nInitially '''BOF''' was set up with technologies machines, equipment and support facilities from China,  but gradually technology transfers from [[Austria]], [[Australia]], [[Belgium]], [[Germany]] & [[Italy]] were added. '''BOF''' now boasts a mix of conventional and state of the art computerized controlled processes/systems for manufacturing.\n\n==Factories==\nBangladesh Ordnance Factories currently operates the following factories.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/about.php |title=B.O.F. - About Us |access-date=2010-10-24 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120723130334/http://www.bof.gov.bd/about.php |archive-date=2012-07-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n#Small Arms Manufacturing Factory\n#Small Arms Ammunition Factory\n#Ball, Tracer, Blank and API ammunition for Rifle, SMG, LMG and HMG  Manufacturing Factory\n#Rifles Manufacturing Factory\n#Machine Gun Manufacturing Factory\n#Grenade Manufacturing Factory\n#Missile Manufacturing Factory\n#Artillery Ammunition Factory\n#Tools Manufacturing Plant\n\n== Products ==\nThe products of Bangladesh Ordnance Factory are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/capabilities/|title=Capabilities|work=bof.gov.bd}}</ref>\n* [[Type 81 assault rifle|BD-08 assault rifle]]\n* [[SKS#Chinese|Type 56 semi automatic rifle]] \n* [[Heckler & Koch G3|Heckler & Koch G3 Battle Rifle]] - Under ToT\n* [[Type 56 assault rifle]] - Licensed Product\n* [[FN-6#FN-16|FN-16 MANPAD]] - Under ToT\n* Arges-84 Grenade\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bangladesh Machine Tools Factory]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bof.gov.bd Official Site of Bangladesh Ordnance Factories]\n{{Ministry of Defence (Bangladesh)}}\n[[Category:Defence companies of Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies established in 1970]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Gazipur]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Government-owned companies of Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:1970 establishments in Pakistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Bangladesh Ordnance Factories \n| logo = BangladeshOrdnanceFactoriesLogo.png\n| logo_size  = 150px\n| logo_alt  =\n| logo_caption  =\n| native_name  = {{lang-bn|\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6 \u09b8\u09ae\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 \u0995\u09be\u09b0\u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09be}}\n| type  =  [[State-owned enterprise]]\n| location  = \n| founded  = {{start date and age|1970|4|6}}\n| location_city = [[Gazipur, Dhaka Division|Gazipur]], [[Dhaka Division]]\n| location_country = [[Bangladesh]]\n| area_served  = Bangladesh\n| key_people = \n| products = [[Firearm]]s, [[Artillery]], [[fuse (explosives)|Fuses]], [[Detonators]], [[Explosives]].\n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| owner = [[Bangladesh Army]]\n| num_employees =\n| parent = \n| subsid = \n| division = \n| homepage = [http://www.bof.gov.bd www.bof.gov.bd]\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Bangladesh Ordnance Factories''' '''(BOF)''' is the largest industrial supplier of the [[Bangladesh Army]]. Situated in [[Gazipur]], it produces arms, ammunition, and equipment for the [[Bangladesh Armed Forces]].\n\nThe current Commandant of Bangladesh Ordnance Factories is Major General Sheikh Pasha Habib Uddin, Afwc, psc\n\n==History==\nEstablishment of Bangladesh Ordnance Factory commenced in 1968 with the technical and financial assistance of People's Republic of China. It was inaugurated on 6 April 1970. Although it suffered considerable damage during the [[Bangladesh Liberation War]] in 1971, its capabilities have been restored and expanded since.\n\nIn 1982-1983 BMR (Balancing, Modernization, Replacement) works started which was completed in 1987. After the BMR the yearly production target of the factory was determined to be 2500 rifles and 15million ammunition per annum. Project on establishment of \u2018Automatic Assault Rifle BD-08\u2019 factory was under taken in 2004-2005 and it was successfully implemented in the year 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/|title=Bangladesh Ordnance  Factories|work=bof.gov.bd}}</ref>\n\n==Technology==\nInitially BOF was set up with technologies machines, equipment and support facilities from China,  but gradually technology transfers from [[Austria]], [[Australia]], [[Belgium]], [[Germany]] & [[Italy]] were added. BOF now boasts a mix of conventional and state of the art computerized controlled processes/systems for manufacturing.\n\n==Factories==\nBangladesh Ordnance Factories currently operates the following factories.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/about.php |title=B.O.F. - About Us |access-date=2010-10-24 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120723130334/http://www.bof.gov.bd/about.php |archive-date=2012-07-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n#Small Arms Manufacturing Factory\n#Small Arms Ammunition Factory\n#Ball, Tracer, Blank and API ammunition for Rifle, SMG, LMG and HMG  Manufacturing Factory\n#Rifles Manufacturing Factory\n#Machine Gun Manufacturing Factory\n#Grenade Manufacturing Factory\n#Missile Manufacturing Factory\n#Artillery Ammunition Factory\n#Tools Manufacturing Plant\n\n== Products ==\nThe products of Bangladesh Ordnance Factory are as follows:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bof.gov.bd/capabilities/|title=Capabilities|work=bof.gov.bd}}</ref>\n* [[Type 81 assault rifle|BD-08 assault rifle]]\n* [[SKS#Chinese|Type 56 semi automatic rifle]] \n* [[Heckler & Koch G3|Heckler & Koch G3 Battle Rifle]] - Under ToT\n* [[Type 56 assault rifle]] - Licensed Product\n* [[FN-6#FN-16|FN-16 MANPAD]] - Under ToT\n* Arges-84 Grenade\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bangladesh Machine Tools Factory]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bof.gov.bd Official Site of Bangladesh Ordnance Factories]\n{{Ministry of Defence (Bangladesh)}}\n[[Category:Defence companies of Bangladesh]]\n[[